The paper discusses the challenges and solutions related to the development of decentralized applications using blockchain technology. It covers topics such as digital assets registration, transactions, data structure, privacy, business rules implementation, peer-to-peer networks, ledger replication, consensus-based state validation, scalability, and integrative solutions. These topics are relevant to several computer science sub-categories, including cryptography (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB).
